---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Installation - Red Elements"
  description="How to install and use Red Elements components in your project."
>
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h1 class="scroll-m-20 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Installation</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mt-2">
        How to install and use Red Elements in your project.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Installation
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        Install the components you need using your preferred package manager:
      </p>

      <tabs-root default-value="npm" class="w-full">
        <tabs-list class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-muted p-1 text-muted-foreground">
          <tab-trigger value="npm" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            npm
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="pnpm" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            pnpm
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="yarn" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            yarn
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="bun" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            bun
          </tab-trigger>
        </tabs-list>
        <tab-content value="npm" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="npm install @red-elements/combobox"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="pnpm" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="pnpm add @red-elements/combobox"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="yarn" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="yarn add @red-elements/combobox"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="bun" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="bun add @red-elements/combobox"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
      </tabs-root>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Usage
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        Red Elements components can be used in multiple ways depending on your framework:
      </p>

      <tabs-root default-value="html" class="w-full">
        <tabs-list class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-muted p-1 text-muted-foreground">
          <tab-trigger value="html" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            HTML/JS
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="react" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            React
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="vue" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            Vue
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="svelte" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-background data-[state=active]:text-foreground data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            Svelte
          </tab-trigger>
        </tabs-list>
        <tab-content value="html" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`import '@red-elements/combobox';

// Use the web components directly in your HTML
const html = \`
  <combobox-root>
    <combobox-trigger>
      <combobox-input placeholder="Select an item..." />
    </combobox-trigger>
    <combobox-content>
      <combobox-item value="1">Item 1</combobox-item>
      <combobox-item value="2">Item 2</combobox-item>
    </combobox-content>
  </combobox-root>
\`;`}
            lang="javascript"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="react" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`import {
  ComboboxRoot,
  ComboboxTrigger,
  ComboboxInput,
  ComboboxContent,
  ComboboxItem
} from '@red-elements/combobox';

export function MyCombobox() {
  return (
    <ComboboxRoot>
      <ComboboxTrigger>
        <ComboboxInput placeholder="Select an item..." />
      </ComboboxTrigger>
      <ComboboxContent>
        <ComboboxItem value="1">Item 1</ComboboxItem>
        <ComboboxItem value="2">Item 2</ComboboxItem>
      </ComboboxContent>
    </ComboboxRoot>
  );
}`}
            lang="tsx"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="vue" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`<script setup>
import '@red-elements/combobox';
</script>

<template>
  <combobox-root>
    <combobox-trigger>
      <combobox-input placeholder="Select an item..." />
    </combobox-trigger>
    <combobox-content>
      <combobox-item value="1">Item 1</combobox-item>
      <combobox-item value="2">Item 2</combobox-item>
    </combobox-content>
  </combobox-root>
</template>`}
            lang="vue"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="svelte" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`<script>
  import '@red-elements/combobox';
</script>

<combobox-root>
  <combobox-trigger>
    <combobox-input placeholder="Select an item..." />
  </combobox-trigger>
  <combobox-content>
    <combobox-item value="1">Item 1</combobox-item>
    <combobox-item value="2">Item 2</combobox-item>
  </combobox-content>
</combobox-root>`}
            lang="svelte"
          />
        </tab-content>
      </tabs-root>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Styling
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        All components are unstyled by default. You can style them using CSS, Tailwind, CSS-in-JS, or any styling solution you prefer:
      </p>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`/* Example with CSS */
combobox-root {
  display: block;
  width: 300px;
}

combobox-trigger {
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 8px;
}

combobox-item[data-highlighted] {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
}

combobox-item[data-selected] {
  background-color: #007bff;
  color: white;
}`}
        lang="css"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Framework-Specific Guides
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        For detailed integration instructions with your specific framework or backend system, check out our framework-specific guides:
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">JavaScript Frameworks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Build tools and meta-frameworks for modern web development</p>
          <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/nextjs" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Next.js</a> - React framework with SSR
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/nuxt" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Nuxt 3</a> - Vue framework with SSR
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/sveltekit" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">SvelteKit</a> - Svelte framework with SSR
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/remix" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Remix</a> - React framework focused on web standards
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/astro" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Astro</a> - Content-focused framework
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/angular" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Angular</a> - Enterprise web framework
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/javascript-frameworks/vite" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Vite</a> - Fast build tool for modern web projects
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Backend Templates</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Server-side frameworks serving HTML templates</p>
          <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/backend-templates/go" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Go</a> - html/template with Go
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/backend-templates/rails" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Ruby on Rails</a> - ERB/Slim templates
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/backend-templates/django" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Django</a> - Python template engine
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/backend-templates/express" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Express</a> - Node.js with EJS/Pug/Handlebars
            </li>
            <li class="leading-7">
              <a href="/docs/guides/backend-templates/hono" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Hono</a> - Fast edge-compatible framework
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Next Steps
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        Explore the component documentation to learn about all available components and their APIs:
      </p>
      <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
        <li class="leading-7">
          <a href="/docs/components/combobox" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Combobox</a>
        </li>
        <li class="leading-7">
          <a href="/docs/components/dialog" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Dialog</a>
        </li>
        <li class="leading-7">
          <a href="/docs/components/dropdown" class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4">Dropdown</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
